From 47f5946bb65d45a18bd3afff62d9aaa64e19c30e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tomas Glozar <tglozar@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 20:40:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 118/118] ia64: Handle topology correctly w/o
 SAL_PHYSICAL_ID_INFO

On systems without SAL_PHYSICAL_ID_INFO, identify_siblings() would
return early, causing the topology gathered by PAL_LOGICAL_TO_PHYS
to be ignored.

Fix the code so that the absensce of SAL_PHYSICAL_ID_INFO sets pltid
to zero so that package ID is determined purely according to
info.overview_ppid and the rest of the topology is set correctly.

This fixes a bug where on older Montecito systems, e.g. rx2620, every
core/thread was being seen as a separate socket.

Signed-off-by: Tomas Glozar <tglozar@gmail.com>
---
 arch/ia64/kernel/smpboot.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/ia64/kernel/smpboot.c b/arch/ia64/kernel/smpboot.c
index 2c1dbcb54076..f25756284c54 100644
--- a/arch/ia64/kernel/smpboot.c
+++ b/arch/ia64/kernel/smpboot.c
@@ -809,7 +809,9 @@ void identify_siblings(struct cpuinfo_ia64 *c)
 			printk(KERN_ERR
 				"ia64_sal_pltid failed with %ld\n",
 				status);
-		return;
+
+		/* No SAL_PHYSICAL_ID_INFO, rely on ppid only */
+		pltid = 0;
 	}
 
 	c->socket_id =  (pltid << 8) | info.overview_ppid;
-- 
